metadata.name: Zometric #189
metadata.description:
A journey into geometric shapes.
Real art is not hidden behind complicated and obscure forms. In this collection, we have tried to achieve a unique visual clarity by using the basic visual elements. A pure mixture between piet mondrian and paul klee. A combination of visual language of classical and modern art movements. Over 15 000 combination can be generated.
Made in p5.js

metadata.name: De/Frag #26
metadata.description:
De/Frag is an homage to a classic algorithm in early computer art: Flood Fill. As a teenager in the late '80s, and without any literature, I spent weeks implementing a version for my very own drawing program for the Atari XL. It was the first non-trivial (to me) algorithm which made me want to learn more about data structures, the concept of recursion, divide-and-conquer...

Even though Flood Fill was available in most commercial drawing & office apps of the time, I gained a deep appreciation of the algorithm by building it from scratch myself. 30+ years later I know its aesthetic possibilities are still far from exhausted. This is an invitation for re-exploration by others too!

As with many design algorithms, my primary interest isn't even the final result, but observing the inner workings. I massively slowed down and time-sliced the process for this piece. I do recommend giving each of these unique versions some time to allow them to evolve their ever-changing patterns (Note: each piece never loops!).

metadata.name: Cells - Part 2 #4
Oceans of Anxiety #91
metadata.description:
Fully generated by code on your machine. Variety of palletes and styles hand-picked with love and understanding.

Anxiety comes in waves.
Itâ€™s that sense of unidentifiable dread.
It can feel like youâ€™re in the middle of an ocean on a rocking boat, and on those really bad days there isnâ€™t even a lifebuoy, youâ€™re drowning and canâ€™t catch your breath, time is viscous and moving in slow-motion.

This piece does not set out to necessarily convey only the worst of dealing with anxiety, but also the resolutions and relief when itâ€™s not there, or finally lets you go.

metadata.name: Uncertain Path #7
metadata.description:
Uncertain Path

An ode to the unpredictability of the paths we take in life.

Uncertain Path was created inspired by La Longue Marche (1974), series of acrylic paintings made by Julio Le Parc.

by @code2pixels
May, 2022

Made with p5.js, p5.js-func and bezier.js

--------------------------

RESOLUTION  
Press a number from '1' to '9' to render in various resolutions, being 1, the smallest, and 9 the highest. 

EXPORT IMAGE 
Open live and press 's'
